* [[John Moffatt (actor)|John Moffatt]] in the 1981 [[United Kingdom|British]] television series ''[[Private Schulz]]''.
* [[Hans Meyer (actor)|Hans Meyer]] in the 1982 United States television production ''[[Inside the Third Reich (film)|Inside the Third Reich]]''.
* [[Christopher Heyerdahl]] in the 2000 [[Canada|Canadian]]/U.S. T.V. production ''Nuremberg''.

The character Ernie Kaltenbrunner from the 1985 [[zombie film]] ''[[The Return of the Living Dead]]'' was named after Ernst Kaltenbrunner.<ref>{{cite AV media |people=Philputt, Bill (director) |date=October 2011 |title=More Brains! A Return to the Living Dead |medium=motion picture |language=English |url= |access-date= |format= |time= |location= |publisher= |id= |oclc= |quote= |ref= }}</ref>

In  [[Harry_Turtledove|Harry Turtldove's]] [[Colonization (series)|''Colonization'' series]] Kaltenbrunner serves as the third Führer of the Greater German Reich, following the deaths of Hitler, and Himmler, respectively. He dies in a nuclear attack and is replaced by [[Walter Dornberger]].

